1
00:00:01,550 --> 00:00:04,580
When Śrila Guru Mahārāj heard 
the Vedic aphorism,

2
00:00:04,580 --> 00:00:10,917
“Satyaṃ brūyāt priyaṃ brūyān na brūyāt 
satyam apriyam [Manu-smṛti: 4.138],

3
00:00:10,917 --> 00:00:12,692
that one should always 
speak the truth …”

4
00:00:12,816 --> 00:00:15,500
[Mercy Over Justice]

5
00:00:15,539 --> 00:00:18,285
he said, 
“All right, that. Yes.”

6
00:00:18,285 --> 00:00:22,608
“… and one should speak the truth 
in a pleasing way.” “Yes.”

7
00:00:22,799 --> 00:00:26,401
And it said, “But one shouldn’t speak 
an unpleasant truth.”

8
00:00:26,401 --> 00:00:28,958
And Guru Mahārāj, 
because he’s very candid

9
00:00:28,958 --> 00:00:34,838
and honest, always, 
about his position,

10
00:00:34,838 --> 00:00:41,900
he will say innocently, openly, 
“That didn’t sit well in my heart.

11
00:00:41,900 --> 00:00:44,431
I’m thinking, 
‘No. You should speak the truth,

12
00:00:44,431 --> 00:00:47,999
whatever the consequences are; 
even if it’s unpleasant.’”

13
00:00:47,999 --> 00:00:52,352
But here, it’s Veda; 
it’s divine sound;

14
00:00:52,352 --> 00:00:55,673
Śabda-brahma has come down 
and said,

15
00:00:55,673 --> 00:00:58,601
“Don’t speak 
an unpalatable truth.”

16
00:00:58,626 --> 00:01:00,318
Why?

17
00:01:00,655 --> 00:01:08,366
But he doesn’t have an immediate answer. 
But because he’s so

18
00:01:08,366 --> 00:01:14,110
devoted and dedicated to these things, 
he’s also willing to wait.

19
00:01:14,110 --> 00:01:15,794
That, we have to learn, also.

20
00:01:16,273 --> 00:01:19,847
Later his consideration became,

21
00:01:19,847 --> 00:01:22,847
‘Beauty over power’; 
‘Heart over intellect’;

22
00:01:22,847 --> 00:01:27,255
‘Mercy over justice’; 
‘Substance over form’.

23
00:01:27,255 --> 00:01:28,876
‘Mercy over justice’.

